<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-17T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-17T16:00:00-05:00" n="543" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d543">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">790.5/5–1754: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States
                                        Delegation</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-17T22:00:00+01:00">May 17, 1954—10
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 79. Repeated information
                                Paris 286, London 176. Paris eyes only Ambassador. London eyes only
                                Ambassador. Re <gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 77, repeated
                                Paris 283.<note n="1" xml:id="d543fn1">Dated May 17, <ref target="#pg_835">p. 835</ref>.</note>
                                <persName corresp="#p_CSHA1">Caccia</persName> has just informed us
                                that <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> has gotten off
                                telegram to London recommending approval of immediate start of
                                five-power military staff talks. He has asked for reply by tomorrow
                                and believes it will be favorable. His only reservation will be that
                                    <pb facs="0864" n="838" xml:id="pg_838"/> committee which is to
                                start its work in Washington should have power to move to meeting
                                place other than Washington if later developments would indicate
                                such move desirable.</p>
                            <p>Re <gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 76, (repeated Paris 282,
                                London 173) <persName corresp="#p_CSHA1">Caccia</persName> reported
                                subject had gone well in Parliament this afternoon.<note n="2" xml:id="d543fn2">For summary of telegram <gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 76, May 17, see <ref target="#pg_816">footnote 2, p. 816</ref>.</note></p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_SWB1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>